6349 // we should actually be checking the type of the template argument in P,
6350 // not the type of the template argument deduced from A, against the
6351 // template parameter type.
6352 Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_deduced_non_type_template_arg_type_mismatch)
6353 << Arg->getType()
6354 << ParamType.getUnqualifiedType();
6355 Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::note_template_param_here);
6356 return ExprError();
6357 }
6358
6359 // If either the parameter has a dependent type or the argument is
6360 // type-dependent, there's nothing we can check now.
6361 if (ParamType->isDependentType() || Arg->isTypeDependent()) {
6362 // FIXME: Produce a cloned, canonical expression?
6363 Converted = TemplateArgument(Arg);
6364 return Arg;
6365 }
6366
6367 // The initialization of the parameter from the argument is
6368 // a constant-evaluated context.
6369 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ConstantEvaluated(
6370 *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
6371
6372 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17) {
6373 // C++17 [temp.arg.nontype]p1:
6374 // A template-argument for a non-type template parameter shall be
6375 // a converted constant expression of the type of the template-parameter.
6376 APValue Value;
6377 ExprResult ArgResult = CheckConvertedConstantExpression(
6378 Arg, ParamType, Value, CCEK_TemplateArg);
6379 if (ArgResult.isInvalid())
6380 return ExprError();
6381
6382 // For a value-dependent argument, CheckConvertedConstantExpression is
6383 // permitted (and expected) to be unable to determine a value.
6384 if (ArgResult.get()->isValueDependent()) {
6385 Converted = TemplateArgument(ArgResult.get());
6386 return ArgResult;
6387 }
6388
6389 QualType CanonParamType = Context.getCanonicalType(ParamType);
6390
6391 // Convert the APValue to a TemplateArgument.
6392 switch (Value.getKind()) {
6393 case APValue::None:
6394 assert(ParamType->isNullPtrType());
6395 Converted = TemplateArgument(CanonParamType, /*isNullPtr*/true);
6396 break;
6397 case APValue::Indeterminate:
6398 llvm_unreachable("result of constant evaluation should be initialized");
6399 break;
6400 case APValue::Int:
6401 assert(ParamType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType());
6402 Converted = TemplateArgument(Context, Value.getInt(), CanonParamType);
6403 break;
6404 case APValue::MemberPointer: {
6405 assert(ParamType->isMemberPointerType());
6406
6407 // FIXME: We need TemplateArgument representation and mangling for these.
6408 if (!Value.getMemberPointerPath().empty()) {
6409 Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(),
6410 diag::err_template_arg_member_ptr_base_derived_not_supported)
6411 << Value.getMemberPointerDecl() << ParamType
6412 << Arg->getSourceRange();
6413 return ExprError();
6414 }
6415
6416 auto *VD = const_cast<ValueDecl*>(Value.getMemberPointerDecl());
6417 Converted = VD ? TemplateArgument(VD, CanonParamType)
6418 : TemplateArgument(CanonParamType, /*isNullPtr*/true);
6419 break;
6420 }
6421 case APValue::LValue: {
6422 // For a non-type template-parameter of pointer or reference type,
6423 // the value of the constant expression shall not refer to
6424 assert(ParamType->isPointerType() || ParamType->isReferenceType() ||
6425 ParamType->isNullPtrType());
6426 // -- a temporary object
6427 // -- a string literal
6428 // -- the result of a typeid expression, or
6429 // -- a predefined __func__ variable
6430 APValue::LValueBase Base = Value.getLValueBase();
6431 auto *VD = const_cast<ValueDecl *>(Base.dyn_cast<const ValueDecl *>());
6432 if (Base && !VD) {
6433 auto *E = Base.dyn_cast<const Expr *>();
6434 if (E && isa<CXXUuidofExpr>(E)) {
6435 Converted = TemplateArgument(ArgResult.get()->IgnoreImpCasts());
6436 break;
6437 }
6438 Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_template_arg_not_decl_ref)
6439 << Arg->getSourceRange();
6440 return ExprError();
6441 }
6442 // -- a subobject
6443 if (Value.hasLValuePath() && Value.getLValuePath().size() == 1 &&
6444 VD && VD->getType()->isArrayType() &&
6445 Value.getLValuePath()[0].getAsArrayIndex() == 0 &&
6446 !Value.isLValueOnePastTheEnd() && ParamType->isPointerType()) {
6447 // Per defect report (no number yet):
6448 // ... other than a pointer to the first element of a complete array
6449 // object.
6450 } else if (!Value.hasLValuePath() || Value.getLValuePath().size() ||
6451 Value.isLValueOnePastTheEnd()) {
6452 Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_non_type_template_arg_subobject)
6453 << Value.getAsString(Context, ParamType);
6454 return ExprError();
6455 }
6456 assert((VD || !ParamType->isReferenceType()) &&
6457 "null reference should not be a constant expression");
6458 assert((!VD || !ParamType->isNullPtrType()) &&
6459 "non-null value of type nullptr_t?");
6460 Converted = VD ? TemplateArgument(VD, CanonParamType)
6461 : TemplateArgument(CanonParamType, /*isNullPtr*/true);
6462 break;
6463 }
6464 case APValue::AddrLabelDiff:
6465 return Diag(StartLoc, diag::err_non_type_template_arg_addr_label_diff);
6466 case APValue::FixedPoint:
6467 case APValue::Float:
6468 case APValue::ComplexInt:
6469 case APValue::ComplexFloat:
6470 case APValue::Vector:
6471 case APValue::Array:
6472 case APValue::Struct:
6473 case APValue::Union:
6474 llvm_unreachable("invalid kind for template argument");
6475 }
6476
6477 return ArgResult.get();
6478 }
6479
6480 // C++ [temp.arg.nontype]p5:
6481 // The following conversions are performed on each expression used
6482 // as a non-type template-argument. If a non-type
6483 // template-argument cannot be converted to the type of the
6484 // corresponding template-parameter then the program is
6485 // ill-formed.
6486 if (ParamType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) {
6487 // C++11:
6488 // -- for a non-type template-parameter of integral or
6489 // enumeration type, conversions permitted in a converted
6490 // constant expression are applied.
6491 //
6492 // C++98:
6493 // -- for a non-type template-parameter of integral or
6494 // enumeration type, integral promotions (4.5) and integral
6495 // conversions (4.7) are applied.
6496
6497 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
6498 // C++ [temp.arg.nontype]p1:
6499 // A template-argument for a non-type, non-template template-parameter
6500 // shall be one of:
6501 //
6502 // -- for a non-type template-parameter of integral or enumeration
6503 // type, a converted constant expression of the type of the
6504 // template-parameter; or
6505 llvm::APSInt Value;
6506 ExprResult ArgResult =
6507 CheckConvertedConstantExpression(Arg, ParamType, Value,
6508 CCEK_TemplateArg);
6509 if (ArgResult.isInvalid())
6510 return ExprError();
6511
6512 // We can't check arbitrary value-dependent arguments.
6513 if (ArgResult.get()->isValueDependent()) {
6514 Converted = TemplateArgument(ArgResult.get());
6515 return ArgResult;
6516 }
6517
6518 // Widen the argument value to sizeof(parameter type). This is almost
6519 // always a no-op, except when the parameter type is bool. In
6520 // that case, this may extend the argument from 1 bit to 8 bits.
6521 QualType IntegerType = ParamType;
6522 if (const EnumType *Enum = IntegerType->getAs<EnumType>())
6523 IntegerType = Enum->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
6524 Value = Value.extOrTrunc(Context.getTypeSize(IntegerType));
6525
6526 Converted = TemplateArgument(Context, Value,
6527 Context.getCanonicalType(ParamType));
6528 return ArgResult;
6529 }
6530
6531 ExprResult ArgResult = DefaultLvalueConversion(Arg);
6532 if (ArgResult.isInvalid())
6533 return ExprError();
6534 Arg = ArgResult.get();
6535
6536 QualType ArgType = Arg->getType();
6537
6538 // C++ [temp.arg.nontype]p1:
6539 // A template-argument for a non-type, non-template
6540 // template-parameter shall be one of:
6541 //
6542 // -- an integral constant-expression of integral or enumeration
6543 // type; or
6544 // -- the name of a non-type template-parameter; or
6545 llvm::APSInt Value;
6546 if (!ArgType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) {
6547 Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_template_arg_not_integral_or_enumeral)
6548 << ArgType << Arg->getSourceRange();
6549 Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::note_template_param_here);
6550 return ExprError();
6551 } else if (!Arg->isValueDependent()) {
6552 class TmplArgICEDiagnoser : public VerifyICEDiagnoser {
6553 QualType T;
6554
6555 public:
6556 TmplArgICEDiagnoser(QualType T) : T(T) { }
6557
6558 void diagnoseNotICE(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
6559 SourceRange SR) override {
6560 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_template_arg_not_ice) << T << SR;
6561 }
6562 } Diagnoser(ArgType);
6563
6564 Arg = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(Arg, &Value, Diagnoser,
6565 false).get();
6566 if (!Arg)
6567 return ExprError();
6568 }
6569
6570 // From here on out, all we care about is the unqualified form
6571 // of the argument type.
6572 ArgType = ArgType.getUnqualifiedType();
6573
6574 // Try to convert the argument to the parameter's type.
6575 if (Context.hasSameType(ParamType, ArgType)) {
6576 // Okay: no conversion necessary
6577 } else if (ParamType->isBooleanType()) {
6578 // This is an integral-to-boolean conversion.
6579 Arg = ImpCastExprToType(Arg, ParamType, CK_IntegralToBoolean).get();
6580 } else if (IsIntegralPromotion(Arg, ArgType, ParamType) ||
6581 !ParamType->isEnumeralType()) {
6582 // This is an integral promotion or conversion.
6583 Arg = ImpCastExprToType(Arg, ParamType, CK_IntegralCast).get();
6584 } else {
6585 // We can't perform this conversion.
6586 Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_template_arg_not_convertible)
6587 << Arg->getType() << ParamType << Arg->getSourceRange();
6588 Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::note_template_param_here);
6589 return ExprError();
6590 }
6591
6592 // Add the value of this argument to the list of converted
6593 // arguments. We use the bitwidth and signedness of the template
6594 // parameter.
6595 if (Arg->isValueDependent()) {
6596 // The argument is value-dependent. Create a new
6597 // TemplateArgument with the converted expression.
6598 Converted = TemplateArgument(Arg);
6599 return Arg;
6600 }
6601
6602 QualType IntegerType = Context.getCanonicalType(ParamType);
6603 if (const EnumType *Enum = IntegerType->getAs<EnumType>())
6604 IntegerType = Context.getCanonicalType(Enum->getDecl()->getIntegerType());
6605
6606 if (ParamType->isBooleanType()) {
6607 // Value must be zero or one.
6608 Value = Value != 0;
6609 unsigned AllowedBits = Context.getTypeSize(IntegerType);
6610 if (Value.getBitWidth() != AllowedBits)
6611 Value = Value.extOrTrunc(AllowedBits);
6612 Value.setIsSigned(IntegerType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType());
6613 } else {
6614 llvm::APSInt OldValue = Value;
6615
6616 // Coerce the template argument's value to the value it will have
6617 // based on the template parameter's type.
6618 unsigned AllowedBits = Context.getTypeSize(IntegerType);
6619 if (Value.getBitWidth() != AllowedBits)
6620 Value = Value.extOrTrunc(AllowedBits);
6621 Value.setIsSigned(IntegerType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType());
6622
6623 // Complain if an unsigned parameter received a negative value.
6624 if (IntegerType->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()
6625 && (OldValue.isSigned() && OldValue.isNegative())) {
6626 Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_template_arg_negative)
6627 << OldValue.toString(10) << Value.toString(10) << Param->getType()
6628 << Arg->getSourceRange();
6629 Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::note_template_param_here);
6630 }
6631
6632 // Complain if we overflowed the template parameter's type.
6633 unsigned RequiredBits;
6634 if (IntegerType->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType())
6635 RequiredBits = OldValue.getActiveBits();
6636 else if (OldValue.isUnsigned())
6637 RequiredBits = OldValue.getActiveBits() + 1;
6638 else
6639 RequiredBits = OldValue.getMinSignedBits();
6640 if (RequiredBits > AllowedBits) {
6641 Diag(Arg->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_template_arg_too_large)
6642 << OldValue.toString(10) << Value.toString(10) << Param->getType()
6643 << Arg->getSourceRange();
6644 Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::note_template_param_here);
6645 }
6646 }
6647
6648 Converted = TemplateArgument(Context, Value,
6649 ParamType->isEnumeralType()
6650 ? Context.getCanonicalType(ParamType)
6651 : IntegerType);
6652 return Arg;
6653 }
6654
6655 QualType ArgType = Arg->getType();
6656 DeclAccessPair FoundResult; // temporary for ResolveOverloadedFunction
6657
6658 // Handle pointer-to-function, reference-to-function, and
6659 // pointer-to-member-function all in (roughly) the same way.
6660 if (// -- For a non-type template-parameter of type pointer to
6661 // function, only the function-to-pointer conversion (4.3) is
6662 // applied. If the template-argument represents a set of
6663 // overloaded functions (or a pointer to such), the matching
6664 // function is selected from the set (13.4).
6665 (ParamType->isPointerType() &&
6666 ParamType->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->isFunctionType()) ||
6667 // -- For a non-type template-parameter of type reference to
6668 // function, no conversions apply. If the template-argument
6669 // represents a set of overloaded functions, the matching
6670 // function is selected from the set (13.4).
6671 (ParamType->isReferenceType() &&
6672 ParamType->getAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeType()->isFunctionType()) ||
6673 // -- For a non-type template-parameter of type pointer to
6674 // member function, no conversions apply. If the
6675 // template-argument represents a set of overloaded member
6676 // functions, the matching member function is selected from
6677 // the set (13.4).
6678 (ParamType->isMemberPointerType() &&
6679 ParamType->getAs<MemberPointerType>()->getPointeeType()
6680 ->isFunctionType())) {
6681
6682 if (Arg->getType() == Context.OverloadTy) {
6683 if (FunctionDecl *Fn = ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(Arg, ParamType,
6684 true,
6685 FoundResult)) {
6686 if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Fn, Arg->getBeginLoc()))
6687 return ExprError();
6688
6689 Arg = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(Arg, FoundResult, Fn);
6690 ArgType = Arg->getType();
6691 } else
6692 return ExprError();
6693 }
6694
6695 if (!ParamType->isMemberPointerType()) {
6696 if (CheckTemplateArgumentAddressOfObjectOrFunction(*this, Param,
6697 ParamType,
6698 Arg, Converted))
6699 return ExprError();
6700 return Arg;
6701 }
6702
6703 if (CheckTemplateArgumentPointerToMember(*this, Param, ParamType, Arg,
6704 Converted))
6705 return ExprError();
6706 return Arg;
6707 }
6708
6709 if (ParamType->isPointerType()) {
6710 // -- for a non-type template-parameter of type pointer to
6711 // object, qualification conversions (4.4) and the
6712 // array-to-pointer conversion (4.2) are applied.
6713 // C++0x also allows a value of std::nullptr_t.
6714 assert(ParamType->getPointeeType()->isIncompleteOrObjectType() &&
6715 "Only object pointers allowed here");
6716
6717 if (CheckTemplateArgumentAddressOfObjectOrFunction(*this, Param,
6718 ParamType,
6719 Arg, Converted))
6720 return ExprError();
6721 return Arg;
6722 }
6723
6724 if (const ReferenceType *ParamRefType = ParamType->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
6725 // -- For a non-type template-parameter of type reference to
6726 // object, no conversions apply. The type referred to by the
6727 // reference may be more cv-qualified than the (otherwise
6728 // identical) type of the template-argument. The
6729 // template-parameter is bound directly to the
6730 // template-argument, which must be an lvalue.
6731 assert(ParamRefType->getPointeeType()->isIncompleteOrObjectType() &&
6732 "Only object references allowed here");
6733
6734 if (Arg->getType() == Context.OverloadTy) {
6735 if (FunctionDecl *Fn = ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(Arg,
6736 ParamRefType->getPointeeType(),
6737 true,
6738 FoundResult)) {
6739 if (DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Fn, Arg->getBeginLoc()))
6740 return ExprError();
6741
6742 Arg = FixOverloadedFunctionReference(Arg, FoundResult, Fn);
6743 ArgType = Arg->getType();
6744 } else
6745 return ExprError();
6746 }
6747
6748 if (CheckTemplateArgumentAddressOfObjectOrFunction(*this, Param,
6749 ParamType,
6750 Arg, Converted))
6751 return ExprError();
6752 return Arg;
6753 }
6754
6755 // Deal with parameters of type std::nullptr_t.
6756 if (ParamType->isNullPtrType()) {
6757 if (Arg->isTypeDependent() || Arg->isValueDependent()) {
6758 Converted = TemplateArgument(Arg);
6759 return Arg;
6760 }
6761
6762 switch (isNullPointerValueTemplateArgument(*this, Param, ParamType, Arg)) {
6763 case NPV_NotNullPointer:
6764 Diag(Arg->getExprLoc(), diag::err_template_arg_not_convertible)
6765 << Arg->getType() << ParamType;
6766 Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::note_template_param_here);
6767 return ExprError();
6768
6769 case NPV_Error:
6770 return ExprError();
6771
6772 case NPV_NullPointer:
6773 Diag(Arg->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_cxx98_compat_template_arg_null);
6774 Converted = TemplateArgument(Context.getCanonicalType(ParamType),
6775 /*isNullPtr*/true);
6776 return Arg;
6777 }
6778 }
6779
6780 // -- For a non-type template-parameter of type pointer to data
6781 // member, qualification conversions (4.4) are applied.
6782 assert(ParamType->isMemberPointerType() && "Only pointers to members remain");
6783
6784 if (CheckTemplateArgumentPointerToMember(*this, Param, ParamType, Arg,
6785 Converted))
6786 return ExprError();
6787 return Arg;
6788}
6789
6790static void DiagnoseTemplateParameterListArityMismatch(
6791 Sema &S, TemplateParameterList *New, TemplateParameterList *Old,
6792 Sema::TemplateParameterListEqualKind Kind, SourceLocation TemplateArgLoc);
6793
6794/// Check a template argument against its corresponding
6795/// template template parameter.
6796///
6797/// This routine implements the semantics of C++ [temp.arg.template].
6798/// It returns true if an error occurred, and false otherwise.
6799bool Sema::CheckTemplateTemplateArgument(TemplateParameterList *Params,
6800 TemplateArgumentLoc &Arg) {
6801 TemplateName Name = Arg.getArgument().getAsTemplateOrTemplatePattern();
6802 TemplateDecl *Template = Name.getAsTemplateDecl();
6803 if (!Template) {
6804 // Any dependent template name is fine.
6805 assert(Name.isDependent() && "Non-dependent template isn't a declaration?");
6806 return false;
6807 }
6808
6809 if (Template->isInvalidDecl())
6810 return true;
6811
6812 // C++0x [temp.arg.template]p1:
6813 // A template-argument for a template template-parameter shall be
6814 // the name of a class template or an alias template, expressed as an
6815 // id-expression. When the template-argument names a class template, only
6816 // primary class templates are considered when matching the
6817 // template template argument with the corresponding parameter;
6818 // partial specializations are not considered even if their
6819 // parameter lists match that of the template template parameter.
6820 //
6821 // Note that we also allow template template parameters here, which
6822 // will happen when we are dealing with, e.g., class template
6823 // partial specializations.
6824 if (!isa<ClassTemplateDecl>(Template) &&
6825 !isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Template) &&
6826 !isa<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(Template) &&
6827 !isa<BuiltinTemplateDecl>(Template)) {
6828 assert(isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Template) &&
6829 "Only function templates are possible here");
6830 Diag(Arg.getLocation(), diag::err_template_arg_not_valid_template);
6831 Diag(Template->getLocation(), diag::note_template_arg_refers_here_func)
6832 << Template;
6833 }
6834
6835 // C++1z [temp.arg.template]p3: (DR 150)
6836 // A template-argument matches a template template-parameter P when P
6837 // is at least as specialized as the template-argument A.
6838 if (getLangOpts().RelaxedTemplateTemplateArgs) {
6839 // Quick check for the common case:
6840 // If P contains a parameter pack, then A [...] matches P if each of A's
6841 // template parameters matches the corresponding template parameter in
6842 // the template-parameter-list of P.
6843 if (TemplateParameterListsAreEqual(
6844 Template->getTemplateParameters(), Params, false,
6845 TPL_TemplateTemplateArgumentMatch, Arg.getLocation()))
6846 return false;
6847
6848 if (isTemplateTemplateParameterAtLeastAsSpecializedAs(Params, Template,
6849 Arg.getLocation()))
6850 return false;
6851 // FIXME: Produce better diagnostics for deduction failures.
6852 }
6853
6854 return !TemplateParameterListsAreEqual(Template->getTemplateParameters(),
6855 Params,
6856 true,
6857 TPL_TemplateTemplateArgumentMatch,
6858 Arg.getLocation());
6859}
6860
6861/// Given a non-type template argument that refers to a
6862/// declaration and the type of its corresponding non-type template
6863/// parameter, produce an expression that properly refers to that
6864/// declaration.
6865ExprResult
6866Sema::BuildExpressionFromDeclTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &Arg,
6867 QualType ParamType,
6868 SourceLocation Loc) {
6869 // C++ [temp.param]p8:
6870 //
6871 // A non-type template-parameter of type "array of T" or
6872 // "function returning T" is adjusted to be of type "pointer to
6873 // T" or "pointer to function returning T", respectively.
6874 if (ParamType->isArrayType())
6875 ParamType = Context.getArrayDecayedType(ParamType);
6876 else if (ParamType->isFunctionType())
6877 ParamType = Context.getPointerType(ParamType);
6878
6879 // For a NULL non-type template argument, return nullptr casted to the
6880 // parameter's type.
6881 if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::NullPtr) {
6882 return ImpCastExprToType(
6883 new (Context) CXXNullPtrLiteralExpr(Context.NullPtrTy, Loc),
6884 ParamType,
6885 ParamType->getAs<MemberPointerType>()
6886 ? CK_NullToMemberPointer
6887 : CK_NullToPointer);
6888 }
6889 assert(Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Declaration &&
6890 "Only declaration template arguments permitted here");
6891
6892 ValueDecl *VD = Arg.getAsDecl();
6893
6894 if (VD->getDeclContext()->isRecord() &&
6895 (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(VD) || isa<FieldDecl>(VD) ||
6896 isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(VD))) {
6897 // If the value is a class member, we might have a pointer-to-member.
6898 // Determine whether the non-type template template parameter is of
6899 // pointer-to-member type. If so, we need to build an appropriate
6900 // expression for a pointer-to-member, since a "normal" DeclRefExpr
6901 // would refer to the member itself.
6902 if (ParamType->isMemberPointerType()) {
6903 QualType ClassType
6904 = Context.getTypeDeclType(cast<RecordDecl>(VD->getDeclContext()));
6905 NestedNameSpecifier *Qualifier
6906 = NestedNameSpecifier::Create(Context, nullptr, false,
6907 ClassType.getTypePtr());
6908 CXXScopeSpec SS;
6909 SS.MakeTrivial(Context, Qualifier, Loc);
6910
6911 // The actual value-ness of this is unimportant, but for
6912 // internal consistency's sake, references to instance methods
6913 // are r-values.
6914 ExprValueKind VK = VK_LValue;
6915 if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(VD) && cast<CXXMethodDecl>(VD)->isInstance())
6916 VK = VK_RValue;
6917
6918 ExprResult RefExpr = BuildDeclRefExpr(VD,
6919 VD->getType().getNonReferenceType(),
6920 VK,
6921 Loc,
6922 &SS);
6923 if (RefExpr.isInvalid())
6924 return ExprError();
6925
6926 RefExpr = CreateBuiltinUnaryOp(Loc, UO_AddrOf, RefExpr.get());
6927
6928 // We might need to perform a trailing qualification conversion, since
6929 // the element type on the parameter could be more qualified than the
6930 // element type in the expression we constructed.
6931 bool ObjCLifetimeConversion;
6932 if (IsQualificationConversion(((Expr*) RefExpr.get())->getType(),
6933 ParamType.getUnqualifiedType(), false,
6934 ObjCLifetimeConversion))
6935 RefExpr = ImpCastExprToType(RefExpr.get(), ParamType.getUnqualifiedType(), CK_NoOp);
6936
6937 assert(!RefExpr.isInvalid() &&
6938 Context.hasSameType(((Expr*) RefExpr.get())->getType(),
6939 ParamType.getUnqualifiedType()));
6940 return RefExpr;
6941 }
6942 }
6943
6944 QualType T = VD->getType().getNonReferenceType();
6945
6946 if (ParamType->isPointerType()) {
6947 // When the non-type template parameter is a pointer, take the
6948 // address of the declaration.
6949 ExprResult RefExpr = BuildDeclRefExpr(VD, T, VK_LValue, Loc);
6950 if (RefExpr.isInvalid())
6951 return ExprError();
6952
6953 if (!Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(ParamType->getPointeeType(), T) &&
6954 (T->isFunctionType() || T->isArrayType())) {
6955 // Decay functions and arrays unless we're forming a pointer to array.
6956 RefExpr = DefaultFunctionArrayConversion(RefExpr.get());
6957 if (RefExpr.isInvalid())
6958 return ExprError();
6959
6960 return RefExpr;
6961 }
6962
6963 // Take the address of everything else
6964 return CreateBuiltinUnaryOp(Loc, UO_AddrOf, RefExpr.get());
6965 }
6966
6967 ExprValueKind VK = VK_RValue;
6968
6969 // If the non-type template parameter has reference type, qualify the
6970 // resulting declaration reference with the extra qualifiers on the
6971 // type that the reference refers to.
6972 if (const ReferenceType *TargetRef = ParamType->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
6973 VK = VK_LValue;
6974 T = Context.getQualifiedType(T,
6975 TargetRef->getPointeeType().getQualifiers());
6976 } else if (isa<FunctionDecl>(VD)) {
6977 // References to functions are always lvalues.
6978 VK = VK_LValue;
6979 }
6980
6981 return BuildDeclRefExpr(VD, T, VK, Loc);
6982}
6983
6984/// Construct a new expression that refers to the given
6985/// integral template argument with the given source-location
6986/// information.
6987///
6988/// This routine takes care of the mapping from an integral template
6989/// argument (which may have any integral type) to the appropriate
6990/// literal value.
6991ExprResult
6992Sema::BuildExpressionFromIntegralTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &Arg,
6993 SourceLocation Loc) {
6994 assert(Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Integral &&
6995 "Operation is only valid for integral template arguments");
6996 QualType OrigT = Arg.getIntegralType();
6997
6998 // If this is an enum type that we're instantiating, we need to use an integer
6999 // type the same size as the enumerator. We don't want to build an
7000 // IntegerLiteral with enum type. The integer type of an enum type can be of
7001 // any integral type with C++11 enum classes, make sure we create the right
7002 // type of literal for it.
7003 QualType T = OrigT;
7004 if (const EnumType *ET = OrigT->getAs<EnumType>())
7005 T = ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
7006
7007 Expr *E;
7008 if (T->isAnyCharacterType()) {
7009 CharacterLiteral::CharacterKind Kind;
7010 if (T->isWideCharType())
7011 Kind = CharacterLiteral::Wide;
7012 else if (T->isChar8Type() && getLangOpts().Char8)
7013 Kind = CharacterLiteral::UTF8;
7014 else if (T->isChar16Type())
7015 Kind = CharacterLiteral::UTF16;
7016 else if (T->isChar32Type())
7017 Kind = CharacterLiteral::UTF32;
7018 else
7019 Kind = CharacterLiteral::Ascii;
7020
7021 E = new (Context) CharacterLiteral(Arg.getAsIntegral().getZExtValue(),
7022 Kind, T, Loc);
7023 } else if (T->isBooleanType()) {
7024 E = new (Context) CXXBoolLiteralExpr(Arg.getAsIntegral().getBoolValue(),
7025 T, Loc);
7026 } else if (T->isNullPtrType()) {
7027 E = new (Context) CXXNullPtrLiteralExpr(Context.NullPtrTy, Loc);
7028 } else {
7029 auto IntValue = Arg.getAsIntegral();
7030 if (T->isIntCapType())
7031 IntValue = IntValue.extOrTrunc(Context.getIntRange(T));
7032 E = IntegerLiteral::Create(Context, IntValue, T, Loc);
7033 }
7034
7035 if (OrigT->isEnumeralType()) {
7036 // FIXME: This is a hack. We need a better way to handle substituted
7037 // non-type template parameters.
7038 E = CStyleCastExpr::Create(Context, OrigT, VK_RValue, CK_IntegralCast, E,
7039 nullptr,
7040 Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(OrigT, Loc),
7041 Loc, Loc);
7042 }
7043
7044 return E;
7045}
7046
7047/// Match two template parameters within template parameter lists.
7048static bool MatchTemplateParameterKind(Sema &S, NamedDecl *New, NamedDecl *Old,
7049 bool Complain,
7050 Sema::TemplateParameterListEqualKind Kind,
7051 SourceLocation TemplateArgLoc) {
7052 // Check the actual kind (type, non-type, template).
7053 if (Old->getKind() != New->getKind()) {
7054 if (Complain) {
7055 unsigned NextDiag = diag::err_template_param_different_kind;
7056 if (TemplateArgLoc.isValid()) {
7057 S.Diag(TemplateArgLoc, diag::err_template_arg_template_params_mismatch);
7058 NextDiag = diag::note_template_param_different_kind;
7059 }
7060 S.Diag(New->getLocation(), NextDiag)
7061 << (Kind != Sema::TPL_TemplateMatch);
7062 S.Diag(Old->getLocation(), diag::note_template_prev_declaration)
7063 << (Kind != Sema::TPL_TemplateMatch);
7064 }
7065
7066 return false;
7067 }
7068
7069 // Check that both are parameter packs or neither are parameter packs.
7070 // However, if we are matching a template template argument to a
7071 // template template parameter, the template template parameter can have
7072 // a parameter pack where the template template argument does not.
7073 if (Old->isTemplateParameterPack() != New->isTemplateParameterPack() &&
7074 !(Kind == Sema::TPL_TemplateTemplateArgumentMatch &&
7075 Old->isTemplateParameterPack())) {
7076 if (Complain) {
7077 unsigned NextDiag = diag::err_template_parameter_pack_non_pack;
7078 if (TemplateArgLoc.isValid()) {
7079 S.Diag(TemplateArgLoc,
7080 diag::err_template_arg_template_params_mismatch);
7081 NextDiag = diag::note_template_parameter_pack_non_pack;
7082 }
7083
7084 unsigned ParamKind = isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(New)? 0
7085 : isa<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(New)? 1
7086 : 2;
7087 S.Diag(New->getLocation(), NextDiag)
7088 << ParamKind << New->isParameterPack();
7089 S.Diag(Old->getLocation(), diag::note_template_parameter_pack_here)
7090 << ParamKind << Old->isParameterPack();
7091 }
7092
7093 return false;
7094 }
7095
7096 // For non-type template parameters, check the type of the parameter.
7097 if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *OldNTTP
7098 = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(Old)) {
7099 NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *NewNTTP = cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(New);
7100
7101 // If we are matching a template template argument to a template
7102 // template parameter and one of the non-type template parameter types
7103 // is dependent, then we must wait until template instantiation time
7104 // to actually compare the arguments.
7105 if (Kind == Sema::TPL_TemplateTemplateArgumentMatch &&
7106 (OldNTTP->getType()->isDependentType() ||
7107 NewNTTP->getType()->isDependentType()))
7108 return true;
7109
7110 if (!S.Context.hasSameType(OldNTTP->getType(), NewNTTP->getType())) {
7111 if (Complain) {
7112 unsigned NextDiag = diag::err_template_nontype_parm_different_type;
7113 if (TemplateArgLoc.isValid()) {
7114 S.Diag(TemplateArgLoc,
7115 diag::err_template_arg_template_params_mismatch);
7116 NextDiag = diag::note_template_nontype_parm_different_type;
7117 }
7118 S.Diag(NewNTTP->getLocation(), NextDiag)
7119 << NewNTTP->getType()
7120 << (Kind != Sema::TPL_TemplateMatch);
7121 S.Diag(OldNTTP->getLocation(),
7122 diag::note_template_nontype_parm_prev_declaration)
7123 << OldNTTP->getType();
7124 }
7125
7126 return false;
7127 }
7128
7129 return true;
7130 }
7131
7132 // For template template parameters, check the template parameter types.
7133 // The template parameter lists of template template
7134 // parameters must agree.
7135 if (TemplateTemplateParmDecl *OldTTP
7136 = dyn_cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Old)) {
7137 TemplateTemplateParmDecl *NewTTP = cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(New);
7138 return S.TemplateParameterListsAreEqual(NewTTP->getTemplateParameters(),
7139 OldTTP->getTemplateParameters(),
7140 Complain,
7141 (Kind == Sema::TPL_TemplateMatch
7142 ? Sema::TPL_TemplateTemplateParmMatch
7143 : Kind),
7144 TemplateArgLoc);
7145 }
7146
7147 return true;
7148}
7149
7150/// Diagnose a known arity mismatch when comparing template argument
7151/// lists.
7152static
7153void DiagnoseTemplateParameterListArityMismatch(Sema &S,
7154 TemplateParameterList *New,
7155 TemplateParameterList *Old,
7156 Sema::TemplateParameterListEqualKind Kind,
7157 SourceLocation TemplateArgLoc) {
7158 unsigned NextDiag = diag::err_template_param_list_different_arity;
7159 if (TemplateArgLoc.isValid()) {
7160 S.Diag(TemplateArgLoc, diag::err_template_arg_template_params_mismatch);
7161 NextDiag = diag::note_template_param_list_different_arity;
7162 }
7163 S.Diag(New->getTemplateLoc(), NextDiag)
7164 << (New->size() > Old->size())
7165 << (Kind != Sema::TPL_TemplateMatch)
7166 << SourceRange(New->getTemplateLoc(), New->getRAngleLoc());
7167 S.Diag(Old->getTemplateLoc(), diag::note_template_prev_declaration)
7168 << (Kind != Sema::TPL_TemplateMatch)
7169 << SourceRange(Old->getTemplateLoc(), Old->getRAngleLoc());
7170}
7171
7172/// Determine whether the given template parameter lists are
7173/// equivalent.
7174///
7175/// \param New The new template parameter list, typically written in the
7176/// source code as part of a new template declaration.
7177///
7178/// \param Old The old template parameter list, typically found via
7179/// name lookup of the template declared with this template parameter
7180/// list.
7181///
7182/// \param Complain If true, this routine will produce a diagnostic if
7183/// the template parameter lists are not equivalent.
7184///
7185/// \param Kind describes how we are to match the template parameter lists.
7186///
7187/// \param TemplateArgLoc If this source location is valid, then we
7188/// are actually checking the template parameter list of a template
7189/// argument (New) against the template parameter list of its
7190/// corresponding template template parameter (Old). We produce
7191/// slightly different diagnostics in this scenario.
7192///
7193/// \returns True if the template parameter lists are equal, false
7194/// otherwise.
7195bool
7196Sema::TemplateParameterListsAreEqual(TemplateParameterList *New,
7197 TemplateParameterList *Old,
7198 bool Complain,
7199 TemplateParameterListEqualKind Kind,
7200 SourceLocation TemplateArgLoc) {
7201 if (Old->size() != New->size() && Kind != TPL_TemplateTemplateArgumentMatch) {
7202 if (Complain)
7203 DiagnoseTemplateParameterListArityMismatch(*this, New, Old, Kind,
7204 TemplateArgLoc);
7205
7206 return false;
7207 }
7208
7209 // C++0x [temp.arg.template]p3:
7210 // A template-argument matches a template template-parameter (call it P)
7211 // when each of the template parameters in the template-parameter-list of
7212 // the template-argument's corresponding class template or alias template
7213 // (call it A) matches the corresponding template parameter in the
7214 // template-parameter-list of P. [...]
7215 TemplateParameterList::iterator NewParm = New->begin();
7216 TemplateParameterList::iterator NewParmEnd = New->end();
7217 for (TemplateParameterList::iterator OldParm = Old->begin(),
7218 OldParmEnd = Old->end();
7219 OldParm != OldParmEnd; ++OldParm) {
7220 if (Kind != TPL_TemplateTemplateArgumentMatch ||
7221 !(*OldParm)->isTemplateParameterPack()) {
7222 if (NewParm == NewParmEnd) {
7223 if (Complain)
7224 DiagnoseTemplateParameterListArityMismatch(*this, New, Old, Kind,
7225 TemplateArgLoc);
7226
7227 return false;
7228 }
7229
7230 if (!MatchTemplateParameterKind(*this, *NewParm, *OldParm, Complain,
7231 Kind, TemplateArgLoc))
7232 return false;
7233
7234 ++NewParm;
7235 continue;
7236 }
7237
7238 // C++0x [temp.arg.template]p3:
7239 // [...] When P's template- parameter-list contains a template parameter
7240 // pack (14.5.3), the template parameter pack will match zero or more
7241 // template parameters or template parameter packs in the
7242 // template-parameter-list of A with the same type and form as the
7243 // template parameter pack in P (ignoring whether those template
7244 // parameters are template parameter packs).
7245 for (; NewParm != NewParmEnd; ++NewParm) {
7246 if (!MatchTemplateParameterKind(*this, *NewParm, *OldParm, Complain,
7247 Kind, TemplateArgLoc))
7248 return false;
7249 }
7250 }
7251
7252 // Make sure we exhausted all of the arguments.
7253 if (NewParm != NewParmEnd) {
7254 if (Complain)
7255 DiagnoseTemplateParameterListArityMismatch(*this, New, Old, Kind,
7256 TemplateArgLoc);
7257
7258 return false;
7259 }
7260
7261 return true;
7262}
7263
7264/// Check whether a template can be declared within this scope.
7265///
7266/// If the template declaration is valid in this scope, returns
7267/// false. Otherwise, issues a diagnostic and returns true.
7268bool
7269Sema::CheckTemplateDeclScope(Scope *S, TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams) {
7270 if (!S)
7271 return false;
7272
7273 // Find the nearest enclosing declaration scope.
7274 while ((S->getFlags() & Scope::DeclScope) == 0 ||
7275 (S->getFlags() & Scope::TemplateParamScope) != 0)
7276 S = S->getParent();
7277
7278 // C++ [temp]p4:
7279 // A template [...] shall not have C linkage.
7280 DeclContext *Ctx = S->getEntity();
7281 if (Ctx && Ctx->isExternCContext()) {
7282 Diag(TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc(), diag::err_template_linkage)
7283 << TemplateParams->getSourceRange();
7284 if (const LinkageSpecDecl *LSD = Ctx->getExternCContext())
7285 Diag(LSD->getExternLoc(), diag::note_extern_c_begins_here);
7286 return true;
7287 }
7288 Ctx = Ctx->getRedeclContext();
7289
7290 // C++ [temp]p2:
7291 // A template-declaration can appear only as a namespace scope or
7292 // class scope declaration.
7293 if (Ctx) {
7294 if (Ctx->isFileContext())
7295 return false;
7296 if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Ctx)) {
7297 // C++ [temp.mem]p2:
7298 // A local class shall not have member templates.
7299 if (RD->isLocalClass())
7300 return Diag(TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc(),
7301 diag::err_template_inside_local_class)
7302 << TemplateParams->getSourceRange();
7303 else
7304 return false;
7305 }
7306 }
7307
7308 return Diag(TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc(),
7309 diag::err_template_outside_namespace_or_class_scope)
7310 << TemplateParams->getSourceRange();
7311}
7312
7313/// Determine what kind of template specialization the given declaration
7314/// is.
7315static TemplateSpecializationKind getTemplateSpecializationKind(Decl *D) {
7316 if (!D)
7317 return TSK_Undeclared;
7318
7319 if (CXXRecordDecl *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D))
7320 return Record->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
7321 if (FunctionDecl *Function = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
7322 return Function->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
7323 if (VarDecl *Var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
7324 return Var->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
7325
7326 return TSK_Undeclared;
7327}
7328
7329/// Check whether a specialization is well-formed in the current
7330/// context.
7331///
7332/// This routine determines whether a template specialization can be declared
7333/// in the current context (C++ [temp.expl.spec]p2).
7334///
7335/// \param S the semantic analysis object for which this check is being
7336/// performed.
7337///
7338/// \param Specialized the entity being specialized or instantiated, which
7339/// may be a kind of template (class template, function template, etc.) or
7340/// a member of a class template (member function, static data member,
7341/// member class).
7342///
7343/// \param PrevDecl the previous declaration of this entity, if any.
7344///
7345/// \param Loc the location of the explicit specialization or instantiation of
7346/// this entity.
7347///
7348/// \param IsPartialSpecialization whether this is a partial specialization of
7349/// a class template.
7350///
7351/// \returns true if there was an error that we cannot recover from, false
7352/// otherwise.
7353static bool CheckTemplateSpecializationScope(Sema &S,
7354 NamedDecl *Specialized,
7355 NamedDecl *PrevDecl,
7356 SourceLocation Loc,
7357 bool IsPartialSpecialization) {
7358 // Keep these "kind" numbers in sync with the %select statements in the
7359 // various diagnostics emitted by this routine.
7360 int EntityKind = 0;
7361 if (isa<ClassTemplateDecl>(Specialized))
7362 EntityKind = IsPartialSpecialization? 1 : 0;
7363 else if (isa<VarTemplateDecl>(Specialized))
7364 EntityKind = IsPartialSpecialization ? 3 : 2;
7365 else if (isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Specialized))
7366 EntityKind = 4;
7367 else if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(Specialized))
7368 EntityKind = 5;
7369 else if (isa<VarDecl>(Specialized))
7370 EntityKind = 6;
7371 else if (isa<RecordDecl>(Specialized))
7372 EntityKind = 7;
7373 else if (isa<EnumDecl>(Specialized) && S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
7374 EntityKind = 8;
7375 else {
7376 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_template_spec_unknown_kind)
7377 << S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11;
7378 S.Diag(Specialized->getLocation(), diag::note_specialized_entity);
7379 return true;
7380 }
7381
7382 // C++ [temp.expl.spec]p2:
7383 // An explicit specialization may be declared in any scope in which
7384 // the corresponding primary template may be defined.
7385 if (S.CurContext->getRedeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod()) {
7386 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_template_spec_decl_function_scope)
7387 << Specialized;
7388 return true;
7389 }
7390
7391 // C++ [temp.class.spec]p6:
7392 // A class template partial specialization may be declared in any
7393 // scope in which the primary template may be defined.
7394 DeclContext *SpecializedContext =
7395 Specialized->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext();
7396 DeclContext *DC = S.CurContext->getRedeclContext();
7397
7398 // Make sure that this redeclaration (or definition) occurs in the same
7399 // scope or an enclosing namespace.
7400 if (!(DC->isFileContext() ? DC->Encloses(SpecializedContext)
7401 : DC->Equals(SpecializedContext))) {
7402 if (isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(SpecializedContext))
7403 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_template_spec_redecl_global_scope)
7404 << EntityKind << Specialized;
7405 else {
7406 auto *ND = cast<NamedDecl>(SpecializedContext);
7407 int Diag = diag::err_template_spec_redecl_out_of_scope;
7408 if (S.getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt && !DC->isRecord())
7409 Diag = diag::ext_ms_template_spec_redecl_out_of_scope;
7410 S.Diag(Loc, Diag) << EntityKind << Specialized
7411 << ND << isa<CXXRecordDecl>(ND);
7412 }
7413
7414 S.Diag(Specialized->getLocation(), diag::note_specialized_entity);
7415
7416 // Don't allow specializing in the wrong class during error recovery.
7417 // Otherwise, things can go horribly wrong.
7418 if (DC->isRecord())
7419 return true;
7420 }
7421
7422 return false;
7423}
7424
7425static SourceRange findTemplateParameterInType(unsigned Depth, Expr *E) {
7426 if (!E->isTypeDependent())
7427 return SourceLocation();
7428 DependencyChecker Checker(Depth, /*IgnoreNonTypeDependent*/true);
7429 Checker.TraverseStmt(E);
7430 if (Checker.MatchLoc.isInvalid())
7431 return E->getSourceRange();
7432 return Checker.MatchLoc;
7433}
7434
7435static SourceRange findTemplateParameter(unsigned Depth, TypeLoc TL) {
7436 if (!TL.getType()->isDependentType())
7437 return SourceLocation();
7438 DependencyChecker Checker(Depth, /*IgnoreNonTypeDependent*/true);
7439 Checker.TraverseTypeLoc(TL);
7440 if (Checker.MatchLoc.isInvalid())
7441 return TL.getSourceRange();
7442 return Checker.MatchLoc;
7443}
7444
7445/// Subroutine of Sema::CheckTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs
7446/// that checks non-type template partial specialization arguments.
7447static bool CheckNonTypeTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs(
7448 Sema &S, SourceLocation TemplateNameLoc, NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *Param,
7449 const TemplateArgument *Args, unsigned NumArgs, bool IsDefaultArgument) {
7450 for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumArgs; ++I) {
7451 if (Args[I].getKind() == TemplateArgument::Pack) {
7452 if (CheckNonTypeTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs(
7453 S, TemplateNameLoc, Param, Args[I].pack_begin(),
7454 Args[I].pack_size(), IsDefaultArgument))
7455 return true;
7456
7457 continue;
7458 }
7459
7460 if (Args[I].getKind() != TemplateArgument::Expression)
7461 continue;
7462
7463 Expr *ArgExpr = Args[I].getAsExpr();
7464
7465 // We can have a pack expansion of any of the bullets below.
7466 if (PackExpansionExpr *Expansion = dyn_cast<PackExpansionExpr>(ArgExpr))
7467 ArgExpr = Expansion->getPattern();
7468
7469 // Strip off any implicit casts we added as part of type checking.
7470 while (ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(ArgExpr))
7471 ArgExpr = ICE->getSubExpr();
7472
7473 // C++ [temp.class.spec]p8:
7474 // A non-type argument is non-specialized if it is the name of a
7475 // non-type parameter. All other non-type arguments are
7476 // specialized.
7477 //
7478 // Below, we check the two conditions that only apply to
7479 // specialized non-type arguments, so skip any non-specialized
7480 // arguments.
7481 if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(ArgExpr))
7482 if (isa<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(DRE->getDecl()))
7483 continue;
7484
7485 // C++ [temp.class.spec]p9:
7486 // Within the argument list of a class template partial
7487 // specialization, the following restrictions apply:
7488 // -- A partially specialized non-type argument expression
7489 // shall not involve a template parameter of the partial
7490 // specialization except when the argument expression is a
7491 // simple identifier.
7492 // -- The type of a template parameter corresponding to a
7493 // specialized non-type argument shall not be dependent on a
7494 // parameter of the specialization.
7495 // DR1315 removes the first bullet, leaving an incoherent set of rules.
7496 // We implement a compromise between the original rules and DR1315:
7497 // -- A specialized non-type template argument shall not be
7498 // type-dependent and the corresponding template parameter
7499 // shall have a non-dependent type.
7500 SourceRange ParamUseRange =
7501 findTemplateParameterInType(Param->getDepth(), ArgExpr);
7502 if (ParamUseRange.isValid()) {
7503 if (IsDefaultArgument) {
7504 S.Diag(TemplateNameLoc,
7505 diag::err_dependent_non_type_arg_in_partial_spec);
7506 S.Diag(ParamUseRange.getBegin(),
7507 diag::note_dependent_non_type_default_arg_in_partial_spec)
7508 << ParamUseRange;
7509 } else {
7510 S.Diag(ParamUseRange.getBegin(),
7511 diag::err_dependent_non_type_arg_in_partial_spec)
7512 << ParamUseRange;
7513 }
7514 return true;
7515 }
7516
7517 ParamUseRange = findTemplateParameter(
7518 Param->getDepth(), Param->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc());
7519 if (ParamUseRange.isValid()) {
7520 S.Diag(IsDefaultArgument ? TemplateNameLoc : ArgExpr->getBeginLoc(),
7521 diag::err_dependent_typed_non_type_arg_in_partial_spec)
7522 << Param->getType();
7523 S.Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::note_template_param_here)
7524 << (IsDefaultArgument ? ParamUseRange : SourceRange())
7525 << ParamUseRange;
7526 return true;
7527 }
7528 }
7529
7530 return false;
7531}
7532
7533/// Check the non-type template arguments of a class template
7534/// partial specialization according to C++ [temp.class.spec]p9.
7535///
7536/// \param TemplateNameLoc the location of the template name.
7537/// \param PrimaryTemplate the template parameters of the primary class
7538/// template.
7539/// \param NumExplicit the number of explicitly-specified template arguments.
7540/// \param TemplateArgs the template arguments of the class template
7541/// partial specialization.
7542///
7543/// \returns \c true if there was an error, \c false otherwise.
7544bool Sema::CheckTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs(
7545 SourceLocation TemplateNameLoc, TemplateDecl *PrimaryTemplate,
7546 unsigned NumExplicit, ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> TemplateArgs) {
7547 // We have to be conservative when checking a template in a dependent
7548 // context.
7549 if (PrimaryTemplate->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext())
7550 return false;
7551
7552 TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams =
7553 PrimaryTemplate->getTemplateParameters();
7554 for (unsigned I = 0, N = TemplateParams->size(); I != N; ++I) {
7555 NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *Param
7556 = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(TemplateParams->getParam(I));
7557 if (!Param)
7558 continue;
7559
7560 if (CheckNonTypeTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs(*this, TemplateNameLoc,
7561 Param, &TemplateArgs[I],
7562 1, I >= NumExplicit))
7563 return true;
7564 }
7565
7566 return false;
7567}
7568
7569DeclResult Sema::ActOnClassTemplateSpecialization(
7570 Scope *S, unsigned TagSpec, TagUseKind TUK, SourceLocation KWLoc,
7571 SourceLocation ModulePrivateLoc, TemplateIdAnnotation &TemplateId,
7572 const ParsedAttributesView &Attr,
7573 MultiTemplateParamsArg TemplateParameterLists, SkipBodyInfo *SkipBody) {
7574 assert(TUK != TUK_Reference && "References are not specializations");
7575
7576 CXXScopeSpec &SS = TemplateId.SS;
7577
7578 // NOTE: KWLoc is the location of the tag keyword. This will instead
7579 // store the location of the outermost template keyword in the declaration.
7580 SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = TemplateParameterLists.size() > 0
7581 ? TemplateParameterLists[0]->getTemplateLoc() : KWLoc;
7582 SourceLocation TemplateNameLoc = TemplateId.TemplateNameLoc;
7583 SourceLocation LAngleLoc = TemplateId.LAngleLoc;
7584 SourceLocation RAngleLoc = TemplateId.RAngleLoc;
7585
7586 // Find the class template we're specializing
7587 TemplateName Name = TemplateId.Template.get();
7588 ClassTemplateDecl *ClassTemplate
7589 = dyn_cast_or_null<ClassTemplateDecl>(Name.getAsTemplateDecl());
7590
7591 if (!ClassTemplate) {
7592 Diag(TemplateNameLoc, diag::err_not_class_template_specialization)
7593 << (Name.getAsTemplateDecl() &&
7594 isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Name.getAsTemplateDecl()));
7595 return true;
7596 }
7597
7598 bool isMemberSpecialization = false;
7599 bool isPartialSpecialization = false;
7600
7601 // Check the validity of the template headers that introduce this
7602 // template.
7603 // FIXME: We probably shouldn't complain about these headers for
7604 // friend declarations.
7605 bool Invalid = false;
7606 TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams =
7607 MatchTemplateParametersToScopeSpecifier(
7608 KWLoc, TemplateNameLoc, SS, &TemplateId,
7609 TemplateParameterLists, TUK == TUK_Friend, isMemberSpecialization,
7610 Invalid);
7611 if (Invalid)
7612 return true;
7613
7614 if (TemplateParams && TemplateParams->size() > 0) {
7615 isPartialSpecialization = true;
7616
7617 if (TUK == TUK_Friend) {
7618 Diag(KWLoc, diag::err_partial_specialization_friend)
7619 << SourceRange(LAngleLoc, RAngleLoc);
7620 return true;
7621 }
7622
7623 // C++ [temp.class.spec]p10:
7624 // The template parameter list of a specialization shall not
7625 // contain default template argument values.
7626 for (unsigned I = 0, N = TemplateParams->size(); I != N; ++I) {
7627 Decl *Param = TemplateParams->getParam(I);
7628 if (TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Param)) {
7629 if (TTP->hasDefaultArgument()) {
7630 Diag(TTP->getDefaultArgumentLoc(),
7631 diag::err_default_arg_in_partial_spec);
7632 TTP->removeDefaultArgument();
7633 }
7634 } else if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *NTTP
7635 = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(Param)) {
7636 if (Expr *DefArg = NTTP->getDefaultArgument()) {
7637 Diag(NTTP->getDefaultArgumentLoc(),
7638 diag::err_default_arg_in_partial_spec)
7639 << DefArg->getSourceRange();
7640 NTTP->removeDefaultArgument();
7641 }
7642 } else {
7643 TemplateTemplateParmDecl *TTP = cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Param);
7644 if (TTP->hasDefaultArgument()) {
7645 Diag(TTP->getDefaultArgument().getLocation(),
7646 diag::err_default_arg_in_partial_spec)
7647 << TTP->getDefaultArgument().getSourceRange();
7648 TTP->removeDefaultArgument();
7649 }
7650 }
7651 }
7652 } else if (TemplateParams) {
7653 if (TUK == TUK_Friend)
7654 Diag(KWLoc, diag::err_template_spec_friend)
7655 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(
7656 SourceRange(TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc(),
7657 TemplateParams->getRAngleLoc()))
7658 << SourceRange(LAngleLoc, RAngleLoc);
7659 } else {
7660 assert(TUK == TUK_Friend && "should have a 'template<>' for this decl");
7661 }
7662
7663 // Check that the specialization uses the same tag kind as the
7664 // original template.
7665 TagTypeKind Kind = TypeWithKeyword::getTagTypeKindForTypeSpec(TagSpec);
7666 assert(Kind != TTK_Enum && "Invalid enum tag in class template spec!");
7667 if (!isAcceptableTagRedeclaration(ClassTemplate->getTemplatedDecl(),
7668 Kind, TUK == TUK_Definition, KWLoc,
7669 ClassTemplate->getIdentifier())) {
7670 Diag(KWLoc, diag::err_use_with_wrong_tag)
7671 << ClassTemplate
7672 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(KWLoc,
7673 ClassTemplate->getTemplatedDecl()->getKindName());
7674 Diag(ClassTemplate->getTemplatedDecl()->getLocation(),
7675 diag::note_previous_use);
7676 Kind = ClassTemplate->getTemplatedDecl()->getTagKind();
7677 }
7678
7679 // Translate the parser's template argument list in our AST format.
7680 TemplateArgumentListInfo TemplateArgs =
7681 makeTemplateArgumentListInfo(*this, TemplateId);
7682
7683 // Check for unexpanded parameter packs in any of the template arguments.
7684 for (unsigned I = 0, N = TemplateArgs.size(); I != N; ++I)
7685 if (DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(TemplateArgs[I],
7686 UPPC_PartialSpecialization))
7687 return true;
7688
7689 // Check that the template argument list is well-formed for this
7690 // template.
7691 SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> Converted;
7692 if (CheckTemplateArgumentList(ClassTemplate, TemplateNameLoc,
7693 TemplateArgs, false, Converted))
7694 return true;
7695
7696 // Find the class template (partial) specialization declaration that
7697 // corresponds to these arguments.
7698 if (isPartialSpecialization) {
7699 if (CheckTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs(TemplateNameLoc, ClassTemplate,
7700 TemplateArgs.size(), Converted))
7701 return true;
7702
7703 // FIXME: Move this to CheckTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs so we
7704 // also do it during instantiation.
7705 bool InstantiationDependent;
7706 if (!Name.isDependent() &&
7707 !TemplateSpecializationType::anyDependentTemplateArguments(
7708 TemplateArgs.arguments(), InstantiationDependent)) {
7709 Diag(TemplateNameLoc, diag::err_partial_spec_fully_specialized)
7710 << ClassTemplate->getDeclName();
7711 isPartialSpecialization = false;
7712 }
7713 }
7714
7715 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
7716 ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *PrevDecl = nullptr;
7717
7718 if (isPartialSpecialization)
7719 // FIXME: Template parameter list matters, too
7720 PrevDecl = ClassTemplate->findPartialSpecialization(Converted, InsertPos);
7721 else
7722 PrevDecl = ClassTemplate->findSpecialization(Converted, InsertPos);
7723
7724 ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *Specialization = nullptr;
7725
7726 // Check whether we can declare a class template specialization in
7727 // the current scope.
7728 if (TUK != TUK_Friend &&
7729 CheckTemplateSpecializationScope(*this, ClassTemplate, PrevDecl,
7730 TemplateNameLoc,
7731 isPartialSpecialization))
7732 return true;
7733
7734 // The canonical type
7735 QualType CanonType;
7736 if (isPartialSpecialization) {
7737 // Build the canonical type that describes the converted template
7738 // arguments of the class template partial specialization.
7739 TemplateName CanonTemplate = Context.getCanonicalTemplateName(Name);
7740 CanonType = Context.getTemplateSpecializationType(CanonTemplate,
7741 Converted);
7742
7743 if (Context.hasSameType(CanonType,
7744 ClassTemplate->getInjectedClassNameSpecialization())) {
7745 // C++ [temp.class.spec]p9b3:
7746 //
7747 // -- The argument list of the specialization shall not be identical
7748 // to the implicit argument list of the primary template.
7749 //
7750 // This rule has since been removed, because it's redundant given DR1495,
7751 // but we keep it because it produces better diagnostics and recovery.
7752 Diag(TemplateNameLoc, diag::err_partial_spec_args_match_primary_template)
7753 << /*class template*/0 << (TUK == TUK_Definition)
7754 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(LAngleLoc, RAngleLoc));
7755 return CheckClassTemplate(S, TagSpec, TUK, KWLoc, SS,
7756 ClassTemplate->getIdentifier(),
7757 TemplateNameLoc,
7758 Attr,
7759 TemplateParams,
7760 AS_none, /*ModulePrivateLoc=*/SourceLocation(),
7761 /*FriendLoc*/SourceLocation(),
7762 TemplateParameterLists.size() - 1,
7763 TemplateParameterLists.data());
7764 }
7765
7766 // Create a new class template partial specialization declaration node.
7767 ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *PrevPartial
7768 = cast_or_null<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(PrevDecl);
7769 ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *Partial
7770 = ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl::Create(Context, Kind,
7771 ClassTemplate->getDeclContext(),
7772 KWLoc, TemplateNameLoc,
7773 TemplateParams,
7774 ClassTemplate,
7775 Converted,
7776 TemplateArgs,
7777 CanonType,
7778 PrevPartial);
7779 SetNestedNameSpecifier(*this, Partial, SS);
7780 if (TemplateParameterLists.size() > 1 && SS.isSet()) {
7781 Partial->setTemplateParameterListsInfo(
7782 Context, TemplateParameterLists.drop_back(1));
7783 }
7784
7785 if (!PrevPartial)
7786 ClassTemplate->AddPartialSpecialization(Partial, InsertPos);
7787 Specialization = Partial;
7788
7789 // If we are providing an explicit specialization of a member class
7790 // template specialization, make a note of that.
7791 if (PrevPartial && PrevPartial->getInstantiatedFromMember())
7792 PrevPartial->setMemberSpecialization();
7793
7794 CheckTemplatePartialSpecialization(Partial);
7795 } else {
7796 // Create a new class template specialization declaration node for
7797 // this explicit specialization or friend declaration.
7798 Specialization
7799 = ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl::Create(Context, Kind,
7800 ClassTemplate->getDeclContext(),
7801 KWLoc, TemplateNameLoc,
7802 ClassTemplate,
7803 Converted,
7804 PrevDecl);
7805 SetNestedNameSpecifier(*this, Specialization, SS);
7806 if (TemplateParameterLists.size() > 0) {
7807 Specialization->setTemplateParameterListsInfo(Context,
7808 TemplateParameterLists);
7809 }
7810
7811 if (!PrevDecl)
7812 ClassTemplate->AddSpecialization(Specialization, InsertPos);
7813
7814 if (CurContext->isDependentContext()) {
7815 TemplateName CanonTemplate = Context.getCanonicalTemplateName(Name);
7816 CanonType = Context.getTemplateSpecializationType(
7817 CanonTemplate, Converted);
7818 } else {
7819 CanonType = Context.getTypeDeclType(Specialization);
7820 }
7821 }
7822
7823 // C++ [temp.expl.spec]p6:
7824 // If a template, a member template or the member of a class template is
7825 // explicitly specialized then that specialization shall be declared
7826 // before the first use of that specialization that would cause an implicit
7827 // instantiation to take place, in every translation unit in which such a
7828 // use occurs; no diagnostic is required.
7829 if (PrevDecl && PrevDecl->getPointOfInstantiation().isValid()) {
7830 bool Okay = false;
7831 for (Decl *Prev = PrevDecl; Prev; Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl()) {
7832 // Is there any previous explicit specialization declaration?
7833 if (getTemplateSpecializationKind(Prev) == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization) {
7834 Okay = true;
7835 break;
7836 }
7837 }
7838
7839 if (!Okay) {
7840 SourceRange Range(TemplateNameLoc, RAngleLoc);
7841 Diag(TemplateNameLoc, diag::err_specialization_after_instantiation)
7842 << Context.getTypeDeclType(Specialization) << Range;
7843
7844 Diag(PrevDecl->getPointOfInstantiation(),
7845 diag::note_instantiation_required_here)
7846 << (PrevDecl->getTemplateSpecializationKind()
7847 != TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
7848 return true;
7849 }
7850 }
7851
7852 // If this is not a friend, note that this is an explicit specialization.
7853 if (TUK != TUK_Friend)
7854 Specialization->setSpecializationKind(TSK_ExplicitSpecialization);
7855
7856 // Check that this isn't a redefinition of this specialization.
7857 if (TUK == TUK_Definition) {
7858 RecordDecl *Def = Specialization->getDefinition();
7859 NamedDecl *Hidden = nullptr;
7860 if (Def && SkipBody && !hasVisibleDefinition(Def, &Hidden)) {
7861 SkipBody->ShouldSkip = true;
7862 SkipBody->Previous = Def;
7863 makeMergedDefinitionVisible(Hidden);
7864 } else if (Def) {
7865 SourceRange Range(TemplateNameLoc, RAngleLoc);
7866 Diag(TemplateNameLoc, diag::err_redefinition) << Specialization << Range;
7867 Diag(Def->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_definition);
7868 Specialization->setInvalidDecl();
7869 return true;
7870 }
7871 }
7872
7873 ProcessDeclAttributeList(S, Specialization, Attr);
7874
7875 // Add alignment attributes if necessary; these attributes are checked when
7876 // the ASTContext lays out the structure.
7877 if (TUK == TUK_Definition && (!SkipBody || !SkipBody->ShouldSkip)) {
7878 AddAlignmentAttributesForRecord(Specialization);
7879 AddMsStructLayoutForRecord(Specialization);
7880 }
7881
7882 if (ModulePrivateLoc.isValid())
7883 Diag(Specialization->getLocation(), diag::err_module_private_specialization)
7884 << (isPartialSpecialization? 1 : 0)
7885 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(ModulePrivateLoc);
7886
7887 // Build the fully-sugared type for this class template
7888 // specialization as the user wrote in the specialization
7889 // itself. This means that we'll pretty-print the type retrieved
7890 // from the specialization's declaration the way that the user
7891 // actually wrote the specialization, rather than formatting the
7892 // name based on the "canonical" representation used to store the
7893 // template arguments in the specialization.
7894 TypeSourceInfo *WrittenTy
7895 = Context.getTemplateSpecializationTypeInfo(Name, TemplateNameLoc,
7896 TemplateArgs, CanonType);
7897 if (TUK != TUK_Friend) {
7898 Specialization->setTypeAsWritten(WrittenTy);
7899 Specialization->setTemplateKeywordLoc(TemplateKWLoc);
7900 }
7901
7902 // C++ [temp.expl.spec]p9:
7903 // A template explicit specialization is in the scope of the
7904 // namespace in which the template was defined.
7905 //
7906 // We actually implement this paragraph where we set the semantic
7907 // context (in the creation of the ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl),
7908 // but we also maintain the lexical context where the actual
7909 // definition occurs.
7910 Specialization->setLexicalDeclContext(CurContext);
7911
7912 // We may be starting the definition of this specialization.
7913 if (TUK == TUK_Definition && (!SkipBody || !SkipBody->ShouldSkip))
7914 Specialization->startDefinition();
7915
7916 if (TUK == TUK_Friend) {
7917 FriendDecl *Friend = FriendDecl::Create(Context, CurContext,
7918 TemplateNameLoc,
7919 WrittenTy,
7920 /*FIXME:*/KWLoc);
7921 Friend->setAccess(AS_public);
7922 CurContext->addDecl(Friend);
7923 } else {
7924 // Add the specialization into its lexical context, so that it can
7925 // be seen when iterating through the list of declarations in that
7926 // context. However, specializations are not found by name lookup.
7927 CurContext->addDecl(Specialization);
7928 }
7929
7930 if (SkipBody && SkipBody->ShouldSkip)
7931 return SkipBody->Previous;
7932
7933 return Specialization;
7934}
7935
7936Decl *Sema::ActOnTemplateDeclarator(Scope *S,
7937 MultiTemplateParamsArg TemplateParameterLists,
7938 Declarator &D) {
7939 Decl *NewDecl = HandleDeclarator(S, D, TemplateParameterLists);
7940 ActOnDocumentableDecl(NewDecl);
7941 return NewDecl;
7942}
7943
7944/// Strips various properties off an implicit instantiation
7945/// that has just been explicitly specialized.
7946static void StripImplicitInstantiation(NamedDecl *D) {
7947 D->dropAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
7948 D->dropAttr<DLLExportAttr>();
7949
7950 if (FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
7951 FD->setInlineSpecified(false);
7952}
7953
7954/// Compute the diagnostic location for an explicit instantiation
7955// declaration or definition.
7956static SourceLocation DiagLocForExplicitInstantiation(
7957 NamedDecl* D, SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation) {
7958 // Explicit instantiations following a specialization have no effect and
7959 // hence no PointOfInstantiation. In that case, walk decl backwards
7960 // until a valid name loc is found.
7961 SourceLocation PrevDiagLoc = PointOfInstantiation;
7962 for (Decl *Prev = D; Prev && !PrevDiagLoc.isValid();
7963 Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl()) {
7964 PrevDiagLoc = Prev->getLocation();
7965 }
7966 assert(PrevDiagLoc.isValid() &&
7967 "Explicit instantiation without point of instantiation?");
7968 return PrevDiagLoc;
7969}
7970
7971/// Diagnose cases where we have an explicit template specialization
7972/// before/after an explicit template instantiation, producing diagnostics
7973/// for those cases where they are required and determining whether the
7974/// new specialization/instantiation will have any effect.
7975///
7976/// \param NewLoc the location of the new explicit specialization or
7977/// instantiation.
7978///
7979/// \param NewTSK the kind of the new explicit specialization or instantiation.
7980///
7981/// \param PrevDecl the previous declaration of the entity.
7982///
7983/// \param PrevTSK the kind of the old explicit specialization or instantiatin.
7984///
7985/// \param PrevPointOfInstantiation if valid, indicates where the previus
7986/// declaration was instantiated (either implicitly or explicitly).
7987///
7988/// \param HasNoEffect will be set to true to indicate that the new
7989/// specialization or instantiation has no effect and should be ignored.
7990///
7991/// \returns true if there was an error that should prevent the introduction of
7992/// the new declaration into the AST, false otherwise.
7993bool
7994Sema::CheckSpecializationInstantiationRedecl(SourceLocation NewLoc,
7995 TemplateSpecializationKind NewTSK,
7996 NamedDecl *PrevDecl,
7997 TemplateSpecializationKind PrevTSK,
7998 SourceLocation PrevPointOfInstantiation,
7999 bool &HasNoEffect) {
8000 HasNoEffect = false;
8001
8002 switch (NewTSK) {
8003 case TSK_Undeclared:
8004 case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
8005 assert(
8006 (PrevTSK == TSK_Undeclared || PrevTSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation) &&
8007 "previous declaration must be implicit!");
8008 return false;
8009
8010 case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
8011 switch (PrevTSK) {
8012 case TSK_Undeclared:
8013 case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
8014 // Okay, we're just specializing something that is either already
8015 // explicitly specialized or has merely been mentioned without any
8016 // instantiation.
8017 return false;
8018
8019 case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
8020 if (PrevPointOfInstantiation.isInvalid()) {
8021 // The declaration itself has not actually been instantiated, so it is
8022 // still okay to specialize it.
8023 StripImplicitInstantiation(PrevDecl);
8024 return false;
8025 }
8026 // Fall through
8027 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
8028
8029 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
8030 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
8031 assert((PrevTSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation ||
8032 PrevPointOfInstantiation.isValid()) &&
8033 "Explicit instantiation without point of instantiation?");
8034
8035 // C++ [temp.expl.spec]p6:
8036 // If a template, a member template or the member of a class template
8037 // is explicitly specialized then that specialization shall be declared
8038 // before the first use of that specialization that would cause an
8039 // implicit instantiation to take place, in every translation unit in
8040 // which such a use occurs; no diagnostic is required.
8041 for (Decl *Prev = PrevDecl; Prev; Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl()) {
8042 // Is there any previous explicit specialization declaration?
8043 if (getTemplateSpecializationKind(Prev) == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization)
8044 return false;
8045 }
8046
8047 Diag(NewLoc, diag::err_specialization_after_instantiation)
8048 << PrevDecl;
8049 Diag(PrevPointOfInstantiation, diag::note_instantiation_required_here)
8050 << (PrevTSK != TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
8051
8052 return true;
8053 }
8054 llvm_unreachable("The switch over PrevTSK must be exhaustive.");
8055
8056 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
8057 switch (PrevTSK) {
8058 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
8059 // This explicit instantiation declaration is redundant (that's okay).
8060 HasNoEffect = true;
8061 return false;
8062
8063 case TSK_Undeclared:
8064 case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
8065 // We're explicitly instantiating something that may have already been
8066 // implicitly instantiated; that's fine.
8067 return false;
8068
8069 case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
8070 // C++0x [temp.explicit]p4:
8071 // For a given set of template parameters, if an explicit instantiation
8072 // of a template appears after a declaration of an explicit
8073 // specialization for that template, the explicit instantiation has no
8074 // effect.
8075 HasNoEffect = true;
8076 return false;
8077
8078 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
8079 // C++0x [temp.explicit]p10:
8080 // If an entity is the subject of both an explicit instantiation
8081 // declaration and an explicit instantiation definition in the same
8082 // translation unit, the definition shall follow the declaration.
8083 Diag(NewLoc,
8084 diag::err_explicit_instantiation_declaration_after_definition);
8085
8086 // Explicit instantiations following a specialization have no effect and
8087 // hence no PrevPointOfInstantiation. In that case, walk decl backwards
8088 // until a valid name loc is found.
8089 Diag(DiagLocForExplicitInstantiation(PrevDecl, PrevPointOfInstantiation),
8090 diag::note_explicit_instantiation_definition_here);
8091 HasNoEffect = true;
8092 return false;
8093 }
8094 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected TemplateSpecializationKind!");
8095
8096 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
8097 switch (PrevTSK) {
8098 case TSK_Undeclared:
8099 case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
8100 // We're explicitly instantiating something that may have already been
8101 // implicitly instantiated; that's fine.
8102 return false;
8103
8104 case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
8105 // C++ DR 259, C++0x [temp.explicit]p4:
8106 // For a given set of template parameters, if an explicit
8107 // instantiation of a template appears after a declaration of
8108 // an explicit specialization for that template, the explicit
8109 // instantiation has no effect.
8110 Diag(NewLoc, diag::warn_explicit_instantiation_after_specialization)
8111 << PrevDecl;
8112 Diag(PrevDecl->getLocation(),
8113 diag::note_previous_template_specialization);
8114 HasNoEffect = true;
8115 return false;
8116
8117 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
8118 // We're explicitly instantiating a definition for something for which we
8119 // were previously asked to suppress instantiations. That's fine.
8120
8121 // C++0x [temp.explicit]p4:
8122 // For a given set of template parameters, if an explicit instantiation
8123 // of a template appears after a declaration of an explicit
8124 // specialization for that template, the explicit instantiation has no
8125 // effect.
8126 for (Decl *Prev = PrevDecl; Prev; Prev = Prev->getPreviousDecl()) {
8127 // Is there any previous explicit specialization declaration?
8128 if (getTemplateSpecializationKind(Prev) == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization) {
8129 HasNoEffect = true;
8130 break;
8131 }
8132 }
8133
8134 return false;
8135
8136 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
8137 // C++0x [temp.spec]p5:
8138 // For a given template and a given set of template-arguments,
8139 // - an explicit instantiation definition shall appear at most once
8140 // in a program,
8141
8142 // MSVCCompat: MSVC silently ignores duplicate explicit instantiations.
8143 Diag(NewLoc, (getLangOpts().MSVCCompat)
8144 ? diag::ext_explicit_instantiation_duplicate
8145 : diag::err_explicit_instantiation_duplicate)
8146 << PrevDecl;
8147 Diag(DiagLocForExplicitInstantiation(PrevDecl, PrevPointOfInstantiation),
8148 diag::note_previous_explicit_instantiation);
8149 HasNoEffect = true;
8150 return false;
8151 }
8152 }
8153
8154 llvm_unreachable("Missing specialization/instantiation case?");
8155}
8156
8157/// Perform semantic analysis for the given dependent function
8158/// template specialization.
8159///
8160/// The only possible way to get a dependent function template specialization
8161/// is with a friend declaration, like so:
8162///
8163/// \code
8164/// template \<class T> void foo(T);
8165/// template \<class T> class A {
8166/// friend void foo<>(T);
8167/// };
8168/// \endcode
8169///
8170/// There really isn't any useful analysis we can do here, so we
8171/// just store the information.
8172bool
8173Sema::CheckDependentFunctionTemplateSpecialization(FunctionDecl *FD,
8174 const TemplateArgumentListInfo &ExplicitTemplateArgs,
8175 LookupResult &Previous) {
8176 // Remove anything from Previous that isn't a function template in
8177 // the correct context.
8178 DeclContext *FDLookupContext = FD->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext();
8179 LookupResult::Filter F = Previous.makeFilter();
8180 enum DiscardReason { NotAFunctionTemplate, NotAMemberOfEnclosing };
8181 SmallVector<std::pair<DiscardReason, Decl *>, 8> DiscardedCandidates;
8182 while (F.hasNext()) {
8183 NamedDecl *D = F.next()->getUnderlyingDecl();
8184 if (!isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D)) {
8185 F.erase();
8186 DiscardedCandidates.push_back(std::make_pair(NotAFunctionTemplate, D));
8187 continue;
8188 }
8189
8190 if (!FDLookupContext->InEnclosingNamespaceSetOf(
8191 D->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext())) {
8192 F.erase();
8193 DiscardedCandidates.push_back(std::make_pair(NotAMemberOfEnclosing, D));
8194 continue;
8195 }
8196 }
8197 F.done();
8198
8199 if (Previous.empty()) {
8200 Diag(FD->getLocation(),
8201 diag::err_dependent_function_template_spec_no_match);
8202 for (auto &P : DiscardedCandidates)
8203 Diag(P.second->getLocation(),
8204 diag::note_dependent_function_template_spec_discard_reason)
8205 << P.first;
8206 return true;
8207 }
8208
8209 FD->setDependentTemplateSpecialization(Context, Previous.asUnresolvedSet(),
8210 ExplicitTemplateArgs);
8211 return false;
8212}
8213
8214/// Perform semantic analysis for the given function template
8215/// specialization.
8216///
8217/// This routine performs all of the semantic analysis required for an
8218/// explicit function template specialization. On successful completion,
8219/// the function declaration \p FD will become a function template
8220/// specialization.
8221///
8222/// \param FD the function declaration, which will be updated to become a
8223/// function template specialization.
8224///
8225/// \param ExplicitTemplateArgs the explicitly-provided template arguments,
8226/// if any. Note that this may be valid info even when 0 arguments are
8227/// explicitly provided as in, e.g., \c void sort<>(char*, char*);
8228/// as it anyway contains info on the angle brackets locations.
8229///
8230/// \param Previous the set of declarations that may be specialized by
8231/// this function specialization.
8232///
8233/// \param QualifiedFriend whether this is a lookup for a qualified friend
8234/// declaration with no explicit template argument list that might be
8235/// befriending a function template specialization.
8236bool Sema::CheckFunctionTemplateSpecialization(
8237 FunctionDecl *FD, TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs,
8238 LookupResult &Previous, bool QualifiedFriend) {
8239 // The set of function template specializations that could match this
8240 // explicit function template specialization.
8241 UnresolvedSet<8> Candidates;
8242 TemplateSpecCandidateSet FailedCandidates(FD->getLocation(),
8243 /*ForTakingAddress=*/false);
8244
8245 llvm::SmallDenseMap<FunctionDecl *, TemplateArgumentListInfo, 8>
8246 ConvertedTemplateArgs;
8247
8248 DeclContext *FDLookupContext = FD->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext();
8249 for (LookupResult::iterator I = Previous.begin(), E = Previous.end();
8250 I != E; ++I) {
8251 NamedDecl *Ovl = (*I)->getUnderlyingDecl();
8252 if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Ovl)) {
8253 // Only consider templates found within the same semantic lookup scope as
8254 // FD.
8255 if (!FDLookupContext->InEnclosingNamespaceSetOf(
8256 Ovl->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()))
8257 continue;
8258
8259 // When matching a constexpr member function template specialization
8260 // against the primary template, we don't yet know whether the
8261 // specialization has an implicit 'const' (because we don't know whether
8262 // it will be a static member function until we know which template it
8263 // specializes), so adjust it now assuming it specializes this template.
8264 QualType FT = FD->getType();
8265 if (FD->isConstexpr()) {
8266 CXXMethodDecl *OldMD =
8267 dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl());
8268 if (OldMD && OldMD->isConst()) {
8269 const FunctionProtoType *FPT = FT->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
8270 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FPT->getExtProtoInfo();
8271 EPI.TypeQuals.addConst();
8272 FT = Context.getFunctionType(FPT->getReturnType(),
8273 FPT->getParamTypes(), EPI);
8274 }
8275 }
8276
8277 TemplateArgumentListInfo Args;
8278 if (ExplicitTemplateArgs)
8279 Args = *ExplicitTemplateArgs;
8280
8281 // C++ [temp.expl.spec]p11:
8282 // A trailing template-argument can be left unspecified in the
8283 // template-id naming an explicit function template specialization
8284 // provided it can be deduced from the function argument type.
8285 // Perform template argument deduction to determine whether we may be
8286 // specializing this template.
8287 // FIXME: It is somewhat wasteful to build
8288 TemplateDeductionInfo Info(FailedCandidates.getLocation());
8289 FunctionDecl *Specialization = nullptr;
8290 if (TemplateDeductionResult TDK = DeduceTemplateArguments(
8291 cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(FunTmpl->getFirstDecl()),
8292 ExplicitTemplateArgs ? &Args : nullptr, FT, Specialization,
8293 Info)) {
8294 // Template argument deduction failed; record why it failed, so
8295 // that we can provide nifty diagnostics.
8296 FailedCandidates.addCandidate().set(
8297 I.getPair(), FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl(),
8298 MakeDeductionFailureInfo(Context, TDK, Info));
8299 (void)TDK;
8300 continue;
8301 }
8302
8303 // Target attributes are part of the cuda function signature, so
8304 // the deduced template's cuda target must match that of the
8305 // specialization. Given that C++ template deduction does not
8306 // take target attributes into account, we reject candidates
8307 // here that have a different target.
8308 if (LangOpts.CUDA &&
8309 IdentifyCUDATarget(Specialization,
8310 /* IgnoreImplicitHDAttributes = */ true) !=
8311 IdentifyCUDATarget(FD, /* IgnoreImplicitHDAttributes = */ true)) {
8312 FailedCandidates.addCandidate().set(
8313 I.getPair(), FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl(),
8314 MakeDeductionFailureInfo(Context, TDK_CUDATargetMismatch, Info));
8315 continue;
8316 }
8317
8318 // Record this candidate.
8319 if (ExplicitTemplateArgs)
8320 ConvertedTemplateArgs[Specialization] = std::move(Args);
8321 Candidates.addDecl(Specialization, I.getAccess());
8322 }
8323 }
8324
8325 // For a qualified friend declaration (with no explicit marker to indicate
8326 // that a template specialization was intended), note all (template and
8327 // non-template) candidates.
8328 if (QualifiedFriend && Candidates.empty()) {
8329 Diag(FD->getLocation(), diag::err_qualified_friend_no_match)
8330 << FD->getDeclName() << FDLookupContext;
8331 // FIXME: We should form a single candidate list and diagnose all
8332 // candidates at once, to get proper sorting and limiting.
8333 for (auto *OldND : Previous) {
8334 if (auto *OldFD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(OldND->getUnderlyingDecl()))
8335 NoteOverloadCandidate(OldND, OldFD, FD->getType(), false);
8336 }
8337 FailedCandidates.NoteCandidates(*this, FD->getLocation());
8338 return true;
8339 }
8340
8341 // Find the most specialized function template.
8342 UnresolvedSetIterator Result = getMostSpecialized(
8343 Candidates.begin(), Candidates.end(), FailedCandidates, FD->getLocation(),
8344 PDiag(diag::err_function_template_spec_no_match) << FD->getDeclName(),
8345 PDiag(diag::err_function_template_spec_ambiguous)
8346 << FD->getDeclName() << (ExplicitTemplateArgs != nullptr),
8347 PDiag(diag::note_function_template_spec_matched));
8348
8349 if (Result == Candidates.end())
8350 return true;
8351
8352 // Ignore access information; it doesn't figure into redeclaration checking.
8353 FunctionDecl *Specialization = cast<FunctionDecl>(*Result);
8354
8355 FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *SpecInfo
8356 = Specialization->getTemplateSpecializationInfo();
8357 assert(SpecInfo && "Function template specialization info missing?");
8358
8359 // Note: do not overwrite location info if previous template
8360 // specialization kind was explicit.
